Caravan are an English band from the Canterbury area, 
founded by former Wilde Flowers members David Sinclair, 
Richard Sinclair, Pye Hastings and Richard Coughlan.
Caravan rose to success over a period of several years 
from 1968 onwards into the 1970s as part of the Canterbury 
scene, blending psychedelic rock and jazz to create a 
distinctive sound like their contemporaries Soft Machine. 
Caravan still remains active as a live band in the 21st 
century.
